{"title":"Letter Written on a Ferry While Crossing Long Island Sound","author":{"name":"Anne Sexton"},"publishDate":"2011-05-06","lines":[{"line":"I am surprised to see","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"that the ocean is still going on.","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"Now I am going back","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"and I have ripped my hand","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"from your hand as I said I would","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"and I have made it this far","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"as I said I would","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"and I am on the top deck now","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"holding my wallet, my cigarettes","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"and my car keys","stanza":1,"number":10},{"line":"at 2 oâ€™clock on a Tuesday","stanza":1,"number":11},{"line":"in August of 1960.","stanza":1,"number":12},{"line":"Dearest,","stanza":2,"number":13},{"line":"although everything has happened,","stanza":2,"number":14},{"line":"nothing has happened.","stanza":2,"number":15},{"line":"The sea is very old.","stanza":2,"number":16},{"line":"The sea is the face of Mary,","stanza":2,"number":17},{"line":"without miracles or rage","stanza":2,"number":18},{"line":"or unusual hope,","stanza":2,"number":19},{"line":"grown rough and wrinkled","stanza":2,"number":20},{"line":"with incurable age.","stanza":2,"number":21},{"line":"Still,","stanza":3,"number":22},{"line":"I have eyes.","stanza":3,"number":23},{"line":"These are my eyes:","stanza":3,"number":24},{"line":"the orange letters that spell","stanza":3,"number":25},{"line":"ORIENT on the life preserver","stanza":3,"number":26},{"line":"that hangs by my knees;","stanza":3,"number":27},{"line":"the cement lifeboat that wears","stanza":3,"number":28},{"line":"its dirty canvas coat;","stanza":3,"number":29},{"line":"the faded sign that sits on its shelf","stanza":3,"number":30},{"line":"saying KEEP OFF.","stanza":3,"number":31},{"line":"Oh, all right, I say,","stanza":3,"number":32},{"line":"Iâ€™ll save myself.","stanza":3,"number":33},{"line":"Over my right shoulder","stanza":4,"number":34},{"line":"I see four nuns","stanza":4,"number":35},{"line":"who sit like a bridge club,","stanza":4,"number":36},{"line":"their faces poked out","stanza":4,"number":37},{"line":"from under their habits,","stanza":4,"number":38},{"line":"as good as good babies who","stanza":4,"number":39},{"line":"have sunk into their carriages.","stanza":4,"number":40},{"line":"Without discrimination","stanza":4,"number":41},{"line":"the wind pulls the skirts","stanza":4,"number":42},{"line":"of their arms.","stanza":4,"number":43},{"line":"Almost undressed,","stanza":4,"number":44},{"line":"I see what remains:","stanza":4,"number":45},{"line":"that holy wrist,","stanza":4,"number":46},{"line":"that ankle,","stanza":4,"number":47},{"line":"that chain.","stanza":4,"number":48},{"line":"Oh God,","stanza":5,"number":49},{"line":"although I am very sad,","stanza":5,"number":50},{"line":"could you please","stanza":5,"number":51},{"line":"let these four nuns","stanza":5,"number":52},{"line":"loosen from their leather boots","stanza":5,"number":53},{"line":"and their wooden chairs","stanza":5,"number":54},{"line":"to rise out","stanza":5,"number":55},{"line":"over this greasy deck,","stanza":5,"number":56},{"line":"out over this iron rail,","stanza":5,"number":57},{"line":"nodding their pink heads to one side,","stanza":5,"number":58},{"line":"flying four abreast","stanza":5,"number":59},{"line":"in the old-fashioned side stroke;","stanza":5,"number":60},{"line":"each mouth open and round,","stanza":5,"number":61},{"line":"breathing together","stanza":5,"number":62},{"line":"as fish do,","stanza":5,"number":63},{"line":"singing without sound.","stanza":5,"number":64},{"line":"Dearest,","stanza":6,"number":65},{"line":"see how my dark girls sally forth,","stanza":6,"number":66},{"line":"over the passing lighthouse of Plum Gut,","stanza":6,"number":67},{"line":"its shell as rusty","stanza":6,"number":68},{"line":"as a camp dish,","stanza":6,"number":69},{"line":"as fragile as a pagoda","stanza":6,"number":70},{"line":"on a stone;","stanza":6,"number":71},{"line":"out over the little lighthouse","stanza":6,"number":72},{"line":"that warns me of drowning winds","stanza":6,"number":73},{"line":"that rub over its blind bottom","stanza":6,"number":74},{"line":"and its blue cover;","stanza":6,"number":75},{"line":"winds that will take the toes","stanza":6,"number":76},{"line":"and the ears of the rider","stanza":6,"number":77},{"line":"or the lover.","stanza":6,"number":78},{"line":"There go my dark girls,","stanza":7,"number":79},{"line":"their dresses puff","stanza":7,"number":80},{"line":"in the leeward air.","stanza":7,"number":81},{"line":"Oh, they are lighter than flying dogs","stanza":7,"number":82},{"line":"or the breath of dolphins;","stanza":7,"number":83},{"line":"each mouth opens gratefully,","stanza":7,"number":84},{"line":"wider than a milk cup.","stanza":7,"number":85},{"line":"My dark girls sing for this.","stanza":7,"number":86},{"line":"They are going up.","stanza":7,"number":87},{"line":"See them rise","stanza":7,"number":88},{"line":"on black wings, drinking","stanza":7,"number":89},{"line":"the sky, without smiles","stanza":7,"number":90},{"line":"or hands","stanza":7,"number":91},{"line":"or shoes.","stanza":7,"number":92},{"line":"They call back to us","stanza":7,"number":93},{"line":"from the gauzy edge of paradise,","stanza":7,"number":94},{"line":"good news, good news.","stanza":7,"number":95}]}